00:16:47.980 --> 00:16:52.160
wear it like a badge of pride in the community.
And that of course is about social studies.

00:16:52.160 --> 00:16:57.481
It's absolutely crucial at that everybody's
in this world together, you

00:16:57.481 --> 00:16:59.930
can look at each other.
You are looking at each other all the time.

00:16:59.930 --> 00:17:05.270
And it's this that validates these achievements.
It's this context that really gives them meaning,

00:17:05.270 --> 00:17:08.279
and quite astonishing
value to people because your peers see everything

00:17:08.279 --> 00:17:11.829
you do.
And you in turn are excited by seeing people

00:17:11.829 --> 00:17:15.350
at the top level by seeing
what could happen.

00:17:15.350 --> 00:17:18.379
There's customizations, you have an enormous
and increasing amount of

00:17:18.379 --> 00:17:20.510
control over your avatar.
And that means you really come to own it.

00:17:20.510 --> 00:17:27.389
If you're bored, you can just go and get a
haircut.

00:17:27.389 --> 00:17:31.980
My wife is a doctor, and she spends quite
an amount of time in the game

00:17:31.980 --> 00:17:35.610
collecting an entire set of items with the
moniker of a physician.

00:17:35.610 --> 00:17:46.171
So she can go around wearing a complete of
a physician set, and she's a

00:17:46.171 --> 00:17:49.220
healer, in the game and in life.
And there's many paths.

00:17:49.220 --> 00:17:52.011
You're thrown into this game, and it's the
one game world, but it's a

00:17:52.011 --> 00:17:55.739
very big and flexible world.
You can choose many different classes.

00:17:55.739 --> 00:18:01.250
You can have many different Orcs.
You can explore and you're rewarded for doing

00:18:01.250 --> 00:18:02.450
each of these things.
Everything is validated.

00:18:02.450 --> 00:18:06.830
Everything is a form of progress.
You want to chat to people, you want to form

00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:13.179
a guild, you want to tag
along with raids, fine.

00:18:13.179 --> 00:18:14.179
You want to go around causing grief, fine.
If you want to go around ganking people, that's

00:18:14.179 --> 00:18:15.179
okay.
Possibly.

00:18:15.179 --> 00:18:16.399
You -- it adapts to people.
And it never stands still whilst it gathers

00:18:16.399 --> 00:18:19.470
a tremendous amount of
data, something which I don't need to tell

00:18:19.470 --> 00:18:20.730
people here about.
And this data is establishing a path because

00:18:20.730 --> 00:18:26.029
 -- and this data, this
information that's really been driving the

00:18:26.029 --> 00:18:30.789
industry forward, at what I
would say is the pretty [INAUDIBLE].

00:18:30.789 --> 00:18:34.900
To come from Space Invaders -- bip, bip, bip
 -- 20 nerdy men interested

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:38.450
in getting five points, to something which
can hold the attention for

00:18:38.450 --> 00:18:43.989
thousands of hours of 12 million people around
the world, or [inaudible], 100 billion users

00:18:43.989 --> 00:18:48.909
or something like Zynga's casual games
with close to 200 million users.

00:18:48.909 --> 00:18:53.239
This is absolutely staggering, staggering
achievement in finding out

00:18:53.239 --> 00:18:56.989
what it is that gets people doing something,
and keep them doing it,

00:18:56.989 --> 00:19:03.519
and wanting to improve.
And it's I think what underlies it, is taking

00:19:03.519 --> 00:19:12.389
all the things that
would put them off and just loosely boosting

00:19:12.389 --> 00:19:19.210
instead their investment
in making all sorts of different kinds of

00:19:19.210 --> 00:19:20.210
progress, making energy.
What does all this mean, then?

00:19:20.210 --> 00:19:21.710
I could talk in generalities about what -- as
I said at the start, it's

00:19:21.710 --> 00:19:25.250
not about putting Pac-Man into the classrooms.
It's not about saying, therefore, everyone

00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:27.269
in a Spanish class ought to
play Warcraft.

00:19:27.269 --> 00:19:30.580
This is absolute rubbish.
It's about recognizing what the underlying

00:19:30.580 --> 00:19:34.669
principles are.
First of all, this is where I think games

00:19:34.669 --> 00:19:38.340
show us a different way of
thinking about people, due to traditional

00:19:38.340 --> 00:19:40.500
learning and training
structure.

00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:45.890
Failures should be frequent, recurrent, recognized,
and free of stigma.

00:19:45.890 --> 00:19:49.190
You should not be failing three or four times
in an hour a test and giving up.

00:19:49.190 --> 00:19:54.659
You should be not succeeding 20 times in the
space of a minute, and

00:19:54.659 --> 00:20:00.639
still having a bit of recognition for that,
getting something for that.

00:20:00.639 --> 00:20:05.009
And just doing it again.
Take a wonderful game on the Playstation 3

00:20:05.009 --> 00:20:06.009
called Flower, by
Jenova Chen and thatgamecompany.

00:20:06.009 --> 00:20:11.249
And this is -- it's not a perfect game but
what it is I think is a

00:20:11.249 --> 00:20:14.780
wonderful way of recasting failure as something
triumphant and

00:20:14.780 --> 00:20:18.489
personal, because you control it by moving,
the weed and moving the

00:20:18.489 --> 00:20:24.359
control around [INAUDIBLE] around, and you
have to pick up other flower

00:20:24.359 --> 00:20:27.389
petals.
And when you start playing this game, as some

00:20:27.389 --> 00:20:31.080
of you may know, it's
almost impossible to control the thing.

00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:34.669
You're -- wind is blowing and the flower petal,
you can spend about 50

00:20:34.669 --> 00:20:37.799
times trying to pick up other petals on the
ground, swooping around

00:20:37.799 --> 00:20:40.450
with the control pad, and it's really very,
very difficult.

00:20:40.450 --> 00:20:44.429
But you don't throw the control across the
room.

00:20:44.429 --> 00:20:48.619
You fail 50 times within about the space of
about two minutes.

00:20:48.619 --> 00:20:50.419
And you pick up your first petal, and then
you start to move, and then

00:20:50.419 --> 00:20:54.130
you start to do other stuff.
And as a bit of spatial training, training

00:20:54.130 --> 00:20:57.020
someone who's never
interacted with a computer before, there are

00:20:57.020 --> 00:21:00.179
plenty of people like this
in the world, just moving something around

00:21:00.179 --> 00:21:04.070
to control something
beautiful on a screen is a very, very good

00:21:04.070 --> 00:21:08.039
way of lowering the bearings
of entry, of teaching people how to access

00:21:08.039 --> 00:21:12.070
this electronic world and
the reason I think that people are unafraid

00:21:12.070 --> 00:21:17.519
to fail 50 times in two
minutes in this game is that there is no stigma

00:21:17.519 --> 00:21:19.299
attached.
That the experience is not punishing you for

00:21:19.299 --> 00:21:24.029
not yet succeeding.
It's merely enticing you with graphics, with

00:21:24.029 --> 00:21:27.009
sounds.
It uses principles of flow as well, so it

00:21:27.009 --> 00:21:30.950
adapts to your own way
of doing things.

00:21:30.950 --> 00:21:37.730
And really, it's a completely different way
of thinking about a problem

00:21:37.730 --> 00:21:39.470
and a skill set.
It draws you on.

00:21:39.470 --> 00:21:41.529
Second, progress should be clear and cumulative,
with multiple paths

00:21:41.529 --> 00:21:44.220
and show increments.
What I'm talking about here is what I was

00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:46.830
saying about a person sitting
in a classroom, desperately trying to read

00:21:46.830 --> 00:21:50.080
through a passage with
absolutely no idea what this means in the

00:21:50.080 --> 00:21:54.029
context of a GCSE or a term
or even a letter.

00:21:54.029 --> 00:21:56.399
Now what you can do in games, for instance,
to take World of Warcraft

00:21:56.399 --> 00:21:57.639
again, first time you play the game, you've
got all the numbers, I was

00:21:57.639 --> 00:22:04.369
talking about all your level and everything
like that, and you are

00:22:04.369 --> 00:22:10.129
plunked in the middle of cities.
Cities like [INAUDIBLE], when you're surrounded

00:22:10.129 --> 00:22:14.159
by people who have been
playing the game for thousands of hours surrounded

00:22:14.159 --> 00:22:19.470
by amazing items.
You can wander as a level five character into

00:22:19.470 --> 00:22:23.869
a level 55 area, and look
at the absolute terrifying monsters in there.

00:22:23.869 --> 00:22:28.090
And people do do this, and this is about knowing
where you're going.

00:22:28.090 --> 00:22:32.529
The entire thing is laid out for you in tiny
increments.

00:22:32.529 --> 00:22:36.220
You can see exactly where you'll be at level
55 or level 60 or level

00:22:36.220 --> 00:22:39.539
65, you can see and start to appreciate what
the end game loot will

00:22:39.539 --> 00:22:43.649
look like, what it might look like.
And this is tremendously incentivizing.

00:22:43.649 --> 00:22:45.570
You can see exactly where you've come from
and measure your progress

00:22:45.570 --> 00:22:50.859
but all of the criteria is listed, everything
from level reputation, you

00:22:50.859 --> 00:22:54.440
take ownership of all of it, you see precisely
where you are on the

00:22:54.440 --> 00:22:56.570
scale.
And this really gives people a tremendous

00:22:56.570 --> 00:23:01.559
sense of choosing where they
want to be, and of choosing to invest the

00:23:01.559 --> 00:23:03.999
activities.
It's like going back to the analogy of the

00:23:03.999 --> 00:23:08.419
school.
Someone in a math class struggling to learn

00:23:08.419 --> 00:23:13.429
about differential
equations, having free to access at any moment

00:23:13.429 --> 00:23:16.739
post-graduate level
mathematics, imagining numbers, all sorts

00:23:16.739 --> 00:23:20.450
of other highly advanced
theories and realizing in the very structure

00:23:20.450 --> 00:23:23.461
of the set-up that what
they're doing now in their very basic way

00:23:23.461 --> 00:23:27.039
is on a spectrum with these
other amazing things.

00:23:27.039 --> 00:23:30.690
You see yourself in context and that is enormously
empowering for

00:23:30.690 --> 00:23:34.259
people to understand exactly how far they've
progressed on the same

00:23:34.259 --> 00:23:38.200
virtual scale towards where they want to be
and towards where they

00:23:38.200 --> 00:23:40.100
might be.
Not everybody gets to the end game of Warcraft,

00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:47.889
but it's a great part
of the game to be able to see where that end

00:23:47.889 --> 00:23:48.889
game is.
Not everybody does a post-graduate degree

00:23:48.889 --> 00:23:51.299
in math, but it's
tremendously inspiring for someone struggling

00:23:51.299 --> 00:23:55.080
with differential
equations to understand on a measure as to

00:23:55.080 --> 00:23:59.019
where this fits in with the
far larger world beyond that, to understand

00:23:59.019 --> 00:24:02.769
the whole spectrum of
things and wholly contextualize their own

00:24:02.769 --> 00:24:07.369
activities and see their
progress bit by bit.

00:24:07.369 --> 00:24:12.740
Finally, fairness and transparency.
You know what everybody else is doing.

00:24:12.740 --> 00:24:17.320
And this is really about the fact of turning
the social dynamic into

00:24:17.320 --> 00:24:20.049
something positive.
So you have your classroom situation when

00:24:20.049 --> 00:24:21.049
nobody knows what happens
until the results of the tests come out and

00:24:21.049 --> 00:24:25.080
then it's all back-biting
and back-stabbing but if you can see in real

00:24:25.080 --> 00:24:30.109
time what everybody else
is doing around you, if you can compare yourself

00:24:30.109 --> 00:24:34.679
to them, then you have
options to collaborate.

00:24:34.679 --> 00:24:39.059
You have options to cooperate.
You have options to learn from other people.

00:24:39.059 --> 00:24:43.119
And one of the interesting things about games
is that people, people

00:24:43.119 --> 00:24:48.210
really don't mind things being hard in the
long term.

00:24:48.210 --> 00:24:52.039
They don't mind the lofty, distant pinnacles
being a long way away.

00:24:52.039 --> 00:24:54.679
If it's completely clear how they and everybody
else are getting there,

00:24:54.679 --> 00:24:57.859
if it's completely clear that the playing
field is level, and it's

00:24:57.859 --> 00:25:01.149
completely clear what they need to do to get
there.

00:25:01.149 --> 00:25:03.799
There's one very interesting innovation in
the new Super Mario Brothers

00:25:03.799 --> 00:25:05.480
Wii -- I don't know if anybody has played
that.

00:25:05.480 --> 00:25:11.700
But it has a very nice feature called the
Super Gauntlet -- and this

00:25:11.700 --> 00:25:18.470
is, if you fail a level eight times in a row
or to fail it, a little

00:25:18.470 --> 00:25:20.869
window pops up at the start and says, "Hi,
you're having difficulty

00:25:20.869 --> 00:25:25.970
with this level.
Would you like us to take you through it?"

00:25:25.970 --> 00:25:34.490
And if you say yes -- you have the option
 -- then the computer takes

00:25:34.490 --> 00:25:38.429
over and controls your character, takes you
through the level.

00:25:38.429 --> 00:25:45.690
And at any moment you can interrupt that and
take over again.

00:25:45.690 --> 00:26:01.480
But what this does -- now you might think
putting this kind of thing,

00:26:01.480 --> 00:26:07.700
it breaks a game, it's brings [INAUDIBLE]
in fact, sort of tremendously

00:26:07.700 --> 00:26:14.019
positive response, it's very, very well done.
Because what it does is, it recognizes the

00:26:14.019 --> 00:26:23.519
point at which someone is
about to give up and intervenes and offers

00:26:23.519 --> 00:26:28.320
them a route to take part in
it.

00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:40.919
Just knowing it's there, is extraordinarily
helpful and having the option to take it out

00:26:40.919 --> 00:26:49.700
it keeps people playing.
It stops you from losing.

00:26:49.700 --> 00:26:59.989
And this is the thing I think that as long
as there isn't a silver

00:26:59.989 --> 00:27:06.870
bullet or a shortcut, as long as there's not
something which negates

00:27:06.870 --> 00:27:12.960
effort, then really the more mechanisms like
this, the better.

00:27:12.960 --> 00:27:20.450
If it's fair for everybody and everybody is
aware what everybody else

00:27:20.450 --> 00:27:33.090
is doing, then supporting people to keep on
the path, to keep engaged

00:27:33.090 --> 00:27:40.519
is a sort of good for the learning environments.
You don't want to lose people.

00:27:40.519 --> 00:27:44.830
And there are some very sophisticated ways
about keeping people engaged

00:27:44.830 --> 00:27:51.039
and aware that the operation is fair.
Really, why is all this --

00:27:51.039 --> 00:27:54.549
Why is all this exciting?
And I think it's exciting because we are at

00:27:54.549 --> 00:28:03.200
the beginning of something.
We look at how far, how fast games have come

00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:09.200
in 40 or 50 years.
And not only games.

00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:14.580
Of course, these are lessons which are being
learned in terms of

00:28:14.580 --> 00:28:50.580
usability and access across all sorts of vehicles.
But I think it is happened more intensely

00:28:50.580 --> 00:28:52.369
and with more incredible
focus in the world of games than anywhere

00:28:52.369 --> 00:28:55.669
else because of the unique
way that games tap into us as learning creatures,

00:28:55.669 --> 00:29:07.590
and because of the
way that they allow us to rephrase failure

00:29:07.590 --> 00:29:16.540
as success.
And I think if you look at what someone is

00:29:16.540 --> 00:29:21.610
doing when they sit down to
use anything from a new piece of software

00:29:21.610 --> 00:29:26.259
to using, to taking, to
learning a new job or trying to learn a new

00:29:26.259 --> 00:29:30.509
skill or trying to get on
something, you can really start to explode

00:29:30.509 --> 00:29:33.600
the concept of learning into
something far more just imbibing data.

00:29:33.600 --> 00:29:37.830
You can take ownership of it.
And these kind of techniques that I think

00:29:37.830 --> 00:29:39.549
underpin games, allow people
to be themselves differently.

00:29:39.549 --> 00:29:44.389
They allow people to be braver.
They allow people to replace the fear and

00:29:44.389 --> 00:29:46.869
uncertainty and lack of
engagement with the ability to make really

00:29:46.869 --> 00:29:53.049
bold moves, to learn from
each other and the ability to take ownership

00:29:53.049 --> 00:29:58.289
of their progress.
And I think as I said, we are at the start

00:29:58.289 --> 00:30:03.370
of something now.
And I will be very excited indeed to see where

00:30:03.370 --> 00:30:06.669
it goes and where it
ends.

00:30:06.669 --> 00:30:15.629
I'm going to throw it open to questions at
this point.

